#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_multiplayerapi.rst:174
msgid ""
"The peer object to handle the RPC system (effectively enabling networking"
" when set). Depending on the peer itself, the MultiplayerAPI will become "
"a network server (check with :ref:`is_network_server "
"<class_MultiplayerAPI_method_is_network_server>`) and will set root "
"node's network mode to master, or it will become a regular peer with root"
" node set to puppet. All child nodes are set to inherit the network mode "
"by default. Handling of networking-related events (connection, "
"disconnection, new clients) is done by connecting to MultiplayerAPI's "
"signals."
msgstr ""

